  "showGrid": true,
  "version": 2,
  "createdAt": "2026-03-29T01:52:26.393Z",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "e580563b-6549-4e16-a0b4-d9ce175efcc3",
      "label": "JFK assassinated in Dallas",
      "isUDE": true,
      "notes": "* President John F. Kennedy was shot at 12:30 p.m. CST on Nov 22 1963. (Warren Commission Report, 1964)\n* Pronounced dead at Parkland Memorial Hospital at 1:00 p.m. (Death Certificate, Dallas County)",
      "x": 380,
      "y": 12
    },
    {
      "id": "e37e1c42-9e99-41ed-9e98-6681be694760",
      "label": "Accurate shots at motorcade",
      "notes": "* Three shots fired within ~6 seconds struck Kennedy & Connally. (Warren Commission, Ch. 3)\n* Bullet impacts aligned with sixth-floor SE window of Texas School Book Depository. (HSCA Report, 1979)",
      "x": 1972,
      "y": 160
    },
    {
      "id": "805d32c6-0735-416d-a80c-ab5f182f44b5",
      "label": "Inadequate protective measures",
      "notes": "* Secret Service had 38 agents in Dallas, fewer than recommended 44. (Warren Commission, Appx F)\n* No agents stationed on rear bumper due to Dallas police motorcycles. (Warren Report, Ch. 2)",
      "x": 340,
      "y": 160
    },
    {
      "id": "d1d30a71-a519-4bd8-a565-3e67e5a7ca5f",
      "label": "Oswald positioned in Depository",
      "notes": "* Oswald seen on sixth floor by coworker at 11:45 a.m. (Testimony of Charles Givens)\n* Rifle & cartridge cases found near SE window. (Warren Commission, CE 510)",
      "x": 2852,
      "y": 308
    },
    {
      "id": "e2516829-79c6-4337-a80c-b17d3b60f62c",
      "label": "Oswald motivated to kill",
      "notes": "* Oswald tried to shoot Gen. Edwin Walker in April 1963. (Warren Report, Ch. 4)\n* Told wife he wanted to make a \"historical mark.\" (Marina Oswald testimony, Warren Commission)",
      "x": 1972,
      "y": 328
    },
    {
      "id": "ed85d25c-6ea5-44e8-978e-10e05264ce87",
      "label": "Oswald employed there",
      "notes": "* Hired as order filler at Depository on Oct 16 1963. (Warren Commission, Ch. 7)\n* Referral came from Ruth Paine via phone call. (Testimony of Ruth Paine)",
      "x": 3092,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "a0b1f540-861f-43c7-8370-dc7911e0d7a5",
      "label": "Oswald's political disillusion",
      "notes": "* Defected to USSR 1959; returned 1962 disappointed. (State Dept. records)\n* Distributed pro-Castro leaflets in New Orleans Aug 1963. (HSCA Appendix 13)",
      "x": 1692,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "bacddf3c-9d47-4ef3-94cc-0aed272c9b1d",
      "label": "Desire for notoriety",
      "notes": "* Kept scrapbook of newspaper clippings on himself. (HSCA Vol. 8)\n* Spoke of wanting \"something that will go down in history.\" (Testimony of George de Mohrenschildt)",
      "x": 1972,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "74f3b646-5905-4bd4-b8e2-ec9558ff5f53",
      "label": "Possible conspiracy role",
      "notes": "* HSCA concluded likely \"probable conspiracy\" based on acoustics. (HSCA Final Report, 1979)\n* No definitive co-conspirators identified. (ARRB Final Report, 1998)",
      "x": 2252,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "3cdb751e-cdd0-45e4-8662-779ec4691fc7",
      "label": "Secret Service unprepared",
      "notes": "* Agents had been drinking until 3 a.m. previous night. (Testimony of Agent Blaine, Warren Commission)\n* Director Rowley later admitted advance work was \"inadequate.\" (US House Appropriations Hearing, 1964)",
      "x": 316,
      "y": 327.2
    },
    {
      "id": "6b386063-5ca3-4f2f-9fe3-86b28b14ac7b",
      "label": "Open-top convertible route",
      "notes": "* 1961 Lincoln SS-100-X used with bubble top removed. (Secret Service Vehicle Logs)\n* Chosen route included 120-degree turn onto Elm, slowing to <15 mph. (Dallas Parade Route, City records)",
      "x": 1132,
      "y": 320
    },
    {
      "id": "ebdc721c-22a6-46fd-8a54-eb6f5b4d64e4",
      "label": "Limited intel on Oswald",
      "notes": "* FBI kept basic file but closed security case Mar 1963. (FBI HQ memorandum, 3/29/63)\n* Agent Hosty knew Oswald worked at Depository but didn't tell Secret Service. (Testimony of James Hosty)",
      "x": 292,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "e87b2807-81fc-4668-a434-e248819d76ed",
      "label": "Complacency from past trips",
      "notes": "* Presidential travel since 1950 had no assassination attempts. (Secret Service Statistical Review, 1963)\n* Agents declined to request closed car in Tampa, Nov 18 1963 trip. (Warren Commission, Appx VIII)",
      "x": 572,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "96e361d7-681a-4afc-851e-b31f73203fb8",
      "label": "Need high public visibility",
      "notes": "* White House staff insisted on open car for crowd engagement. (Testimony of Kenneth O'Donnell, Warren Commission)\n* JFK vetoed protective bubble top citing visibility. (Manchester, \"Death of a President\", 1967)",
      "x": 1132,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "b3fce795-3068-4a55-a2bf-d52925d8d05e",
      "label": "Campaigning in Texas",
      "notes": "* 1964 re-election strategy targeted Southern states. (Democratic Party memos, Sept 1963)\n* Visit aimed to mend rift between Connally and Yarborough. (Warren Commission, Ch. 2)",
      "x": 1132,
      "y": 628
    },
    {
      "id": "49030c37-435b-4e20-993f-939aba850efa",
      "label": "Route publicly disclosed",
      "notes": "* Dallas Times Herald printed final motorcade route on 19 Nov 1963. (Dallas Times Herald, 11/19/63)\n* Secret Service Manual §401 forbade publishing precise routes; rule waived. (HSCA Vol 11, p.529)",
      "x": 1412,
      "y": 308
    },
    {
      "id": "5a52856c-2586-435c-a1f5-a8d36c6b99de",
      "label": "Buildings unscreened",
      "notes": "* Only first two floors of Texas School Book Depository were checked; upper floors skipped. (Warren Report, Appx VIII)\n* SS Advance Agent Lawson testified no manpower to guard every building. (Warren Hearings, Vol IV, p.336)",
      "x": 36,
      "y": 308
    },
    {
      "id": "d88dbc63-1076-4075-befa-7e9f33c953b3",
      "label": "SS staffing shortages",
      "notes": "* FY-1964 request for 65 new protective agents was denied. (US House Appropriations Hearings, 1964)\n* Protective Division overtime averaged 120 hrs/month per agent in 1963. (Secret Service Memo, 8/1963)",
      "x": 852,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "2227a394-6f97-493c-908b-198d20a129cf",
      "label": "Poor threat sharing",
      "notes": "* FBI Agent Hosty knew Oswald worked at Depository but did not alert Secret Service. (WC Vol IV, p.456)\n* CIA 201 file on Oswald was not shared with FBI until after assassination. (CIA IG Report, 1967)",
      "x": 12,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "1f0c0fc1-0530-43c8-97d8-71cc9860126e",
      "label": "Mail-order rifle loophole",
      "notes": "* Oswald ordered 6.5 mm Carcano rifle by mail on 3 Mar 1963 without background check. (CE 773)\n* Loophole later closed by Gun Control Act 1968 banning interstate mail-order firearms. (US Senate Report 90-1097)",
      "x": 1692,
      "y": 308
    },
    {
      "id": "f92f0272-cd94-45ba-b4a5-479c739f3b45",
      "label": "Rifle stored at work",
      "notes": "* Coworker Buell Frazier saw Oswald carry a long paper bag on 22 Nov 1963. (WC Vol II, p.217)\n* Depository had no package-inspection policy for employees. (Warren Report, Ch. 4)",
      "x": 2812,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "94958637-4be0-4970-a6d7-192b02f01a5b",
      "label": "Oswald domestic strife",
      "notes": "* Marina Oswald testified Lee grew \"desperate for significance.\" (WC Vol V)\n* FBI psychological memo labeled him \"socially alienated loner.\" (FBI Malley, 12/2/63)",
      "x": 2532,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "f5583528-bb0f-4932-af27-3537c0da2856",
      "label": "Radical media intake",
      "notes": "* Search recovered copies of The Militant and The Worker from Oswald's room. (FBI Dallas 89-43-1)\n* Oswald borrowed \"Fidel Castro Speaks\" from New Orleans library, July 1963. (HSCA Vol 8, p.245)",
      "x": 1412,
      "y": 480
    },
    {
      "id": "86167f82-2087-48e9-af0b-e5e46a9b7f60",
      "label": "Mend TX Dem rift",
      "notes": "* White House memo 30 Oct 1963 shows JFK \"adamant\" about Texas trip over SS concerns. (NARA, WHCF)\n* RFK letter to Gov. Connally urged unity event in Dallas. (RFK Papers, Box 35)",
      "x": 1132,
      "y": 776
    },
    {
      "id": "a3b0646f-e010-41ce-894f-80def780c857",
      "label": "Success bred complacency",
      "notes": "* SS Director Rowley testified \"Success breeds carelessness.\" (US House Appropriations, 1964)\n* No assassination of a sitting U.S. president since 1901. (Secret Service Annual Review, 1963)",
      "x": 572,
      "y": 628
    }
  ],
